1 AN ACT relating to air pollution control.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢Section 1. KRS 77.070 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) In a county containing a consolidated local government or a city with a population
5 equal to or greater than twenty thousand (20,000) based upon the most recent
6 federal decennial census, the air pollution control board of the air pollution control
7 district shall consist of seven (7) members, three (3) of whom shall be appointed by
8 the county judge/executive, subject to the approval of the fiscal court, and four (4)
9 of whom shall be appointed by the mayor. The mayoral appointments shall be
10 subject to the approval of the legislative body of the city.
11 (2) The mayor shall appoint, subject to the approval of the legislative body of the city,
12 one (1) member for a term of one (1) year, one (1) member for a term of two (2)
13 years, one (1) member for a term of three (3) years, and one (1) member for a term
14 of four (4) years, and the county judge/executive, subject to the approval of the
15 fiscal court, shall appoint one (1) member for a term of two (2) years, one (1)
16 member for a term of three (3) years, and one (1) member for a term of four (4)
17 years, and upon the expiration of each of said terms respectively, and thereafter, the
18 term of each of such members shall be four (4) years, and until their successors are
19 appointed and qualified.
20 (3) All air pollution control board members appointed pursuant to this section must be
21 freeholders within the district; those appointed by the county judge/executive must
22 be residents of such county, and those appointed by a mayor must be residents of
23 their respective city or consolidated local government.
24 (4) Not more than four (4) of the seven (7) board members appointed pursuant to this
25 section shall be of the same political party affiliation, nor shall an officer or
26 employee of such city, consolidated local government, or county, whether holding a
27 paid or unpaid position, be eligible for appointment to the board.
